QUOTE RULES
=================================================================

Direct quotes must be rare and short.

Maximum 15 words per quote.
Maximum one direct quote per underlying source.
Paraphrase everything else.

Every important source item must include:

* source;
* date;
* URL;                          [v1.1] URL is now MANDATORY, not optional
* source type;
* confidence: High / Medium / Low (gated per P1/P4 above).

Do not use messy labels such as:
"Bloomberg + 5"
"ReutersYahooFinance"
"MarketWatchCNBCBloomberg"

If the source cannot be cleanly identified, put the item in "Unverified / possible gaps" and do not let it drive the core conclusion.

=================================================================
WINDOW DISCIPLINE
=================================================================

The monitoring window is binding.

Separate clearly:

* in-window evidence;
* carry-over context;
* unverified material;
* prior-week baseline;
* next-week forward-looking catalyst.

Do not let old narratives dominate the current week unless they were revalidated in the current window.

If a key event happened outside the window but is necessary context, label it as carry-over.

