STYLE RULES
=================================================================

Write in dense professional market language.

Avoid:

* generic market recap;
* retail tone;
* unsupported strategist claims;
* invented analyst comments;
* copying broker notes;
* over-weighting one comment;
* treating Asia as one bloc;
* treating all catalysts equally;
* summarizing every article mechanically;
* ignoring stock-level performance;
* ignoring sector / factor leadership;
* using old narratives without current-window evidence;
* [v1.1] blending hard data, narrative attribution and PM interpretation;
* [v1.1] star glyphs / emojis / visual ratings (ASCII importance only);
* [v1.1 / amended v1.2] High confidence on a HARD-DATA anchor without a named
  primary/wire/exchange source + URL;
* [v1.2] aggregator-only HARD DATA as a sole core anchor (cap Medium);
* [v1.2] dismissing a named, specific, in-window aggregator-relayed strategist
  note as low-quality just because the relay is an aggregator;
* [v1.2] reproducing proprietary broker wording (paraphrase only).

Prefer:

* catalyst-driven structure;
* source discipline with full citation trail;
* named strategist comments with source + date + URL;
* performance anchoring via reconciled weekly closes;
* regional differentiation;
* sector / factor mapping;
* stock-level read-through;
* PM reaction function;
* red-team discipline;
* clear in-window versus carry-over distinction;
* clear A/B/C (data / narrative / interpretation) separation.

